From 11ad773bceb372d228b03f022bed96d0800bc41f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: souliane <21343492+souliane@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 22:37:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(e2e): scope full-worktree provisioning to --target
 local; pin a no-provision remote eval

The e2e skill's full-worktree provisioning rule read as unconditional, so a
--target dev (remote) run could trigger a full local backend/frontend/DB
stand-up the spec never touches. Scope that Non-Negotiable to --target local
and add an explicit --target dev rule: provision nothing, run the spec straight
against the deployed env with t3 <overlay> e2e external --target dev
--test-path <spec>.

Pin the drift with a co-located metered eval
(e2e_dev_target_runs_remote_without_provisioning): the agent must run the
remote spec directly and provision nothing. Ships _fail (provisions before the
dev run -> RED), _pass (runs directly -> GREEN), and _noop (no calls -> RED)
fixtures; the anti-vacuity gate proves the _fail fixture drives the scenario
red on replay.
